commit.message: Update BSD & generic policies to use same SEC_ naming conventions as other policies
update changelog; change param names in some test-harness tests for consistency
Add test-harness tests for new twprint options (verbosity in print-db, object-list in print-report)
Add ability to print report by object list, like we already do w/ print-db mode
Add --output-level/DBPRINTLEVEL to twprint's print-dbfile mode
Update ChangeLog for clang-format stuff
Clean up code formatting with clang-format; add a custom clang-format style that tries to approximate the existing OST code style
Update 'Packaging' file to mention the Dockerfile project I saw recently
Update ChangeLog
More wordsmithing for README.md
Use SEC_ naming convention w/ Solaris policy
Use SEC_ naming convention for OpenBSD (& variants) policies, including new one for LibertyBSD
Use SEC_ naming convention in new policies
Assorted default policy updates
More work on README.md
Add a SkyOS default policy
Use system/popen on Syllable since msystem/mpopen fail there; root cause is still TBD.
Syllable default policy
Default Cygwin policy, and install script tweak to enable it, by using uname -o when uname -s gives us a name in a format we'd rather not use, like 'CYGWIN_NT_10.0'
small Hurd policy tweak
Merge branch 'dev/q1-2018' of https://github.com/Tripwire/tripwire-open-source into dev/q1-2018
Default policy for GNU/Hurd
Add default Minix policy
Change description in Linux policy
